
Thinking in React

Date: 13 Nov 2023

URL: https://react.dev/learn/thinking-in-react


Notes:

    Start with the mockup:

        Imagine you aleady have:

            JSON API

            Mockup from a designer.

    Break the UI into a component hierarchy

        Main div

        Search bar

        Product table

            Product heading

            Product row


    Build a static version


    Find the minimal changes to use varibles for data (State)


    Identify where variables should live

        Component or parent level


    Add state with useState() hooks

        hooks are react functions

        Determine their initial state


    ===

    Adding react to an existing project

    index.html

        <!DOCTYPE html>
        <html>
          <head><title>My app</title></head>
          <body>
            <p>This paragraph is a part of HTML.</p>
            <nav id="navigation"></nav>
            <p>This paragraph is also a part of HTML.</p>
          </body>
        </html>


    index.js

        import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client';

        function NavigationBar() {
          return <h1>Hello from React!</h1>;
        }

        const domNode = document.getElementById('navigation');
        const root = createRoot(domNode);
        root.render(<NavigationBar />);





